{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idd10cb998-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s1521a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1521a"},"text":"§ 1521a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Destruction of existing stockpile of lethal chemical agents and munitions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd10cb999-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s1521a/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Program management","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of Defense shall ensure that the program for destruction of the United States stockpile of lethal chemical agents and munitions is managed as a major defense acquisition program (as defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s4201"},"text":"section 4201 of title 10","children":[],"tail":") in accordance with the essential elements of such programs as may be determined by the Secretary."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd10cb99a-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s1521a/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Requirement for Under Secretary of Defense (Comptroller) annual certification","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Beginning with respect to the budget request for fiscal year 2004, the Under Secretary of Defense (Comptroller) shall submit to the congressional defense committees on an annual basis a certification that the budget request for the chemical agents and munitions destruction program has been submitted in accordance with the requirements of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s1521"},"text":"section 1521 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idd10cb99b-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/314/dA/tI/s141"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–314, div. A, title I, § 141","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-12-02"},"text":"Dec. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/2477"},"text":"116 Stat. 2477","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXVIII/s1846/i/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XVIII, § 1846(i)(6)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4252"},"text":"134 Stat. 4252","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/81/dA/tXVII/s1702/k/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–81, div. A, title XVII, § 1702(k)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/135/2160"},"text":"135 Stat. 2160","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idd10cb99c-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idd10cb99d-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idd10cb99e-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Bob Stump National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2003, and not as part of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/121/tIV/s409"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–121, title IV, § 409","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-11-19"},"text":"Nov. 19, 1969","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/83/209"},"text":"83 Stat. 209","children":[],"tail":", which comprises this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idd10cb99f-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/81"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–81","children":[],"tail":" amended subsec. (a) identically, substituting “section 4201” for “section 2430”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idd10cb9a0-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idd10cb9a1-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2021 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2022","children":[],"tail":", with additional provisions for delayed implementation and applicability of existing law, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1801/d"},"text":"section 1801(d) of Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3001"},"text":"section 3001 of Title 10","children":[],"tail":", Armed Forces."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idd10cb9a2-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"“Congressional Defense Committees” Defined","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Congressional defense committees means the Committees on Armed Services and Appropriations of the Senate and the House of Representatives, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/314/s3"},"text":"section 3 of Pub. L. 107–314","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/2471"},"text":"116 Stat. 2471","children":[],"tail":". See note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 10","children":[],"tail":", Armed Forces."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
